The paper deals with complete lattices and their use in solving fixed point equations, which are topics typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the semantics of logic programs with negation, which falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL). The use of inverse limit representations is a common technique in the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and the paper also discusses the properties of weakly monotone functions, which are relevant to the area of machine learning (cs.LG).
